quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  22,1,Mankind! fear your Lord; verily the quake of the Hour shall be a thing mighty
  22,2,"The Day whereon ye behold it, every suckling woman shall forget that which she suckleth, and every burthened woman shall lay down her burthen; and thou shalt behold mankind as drunken, whereas drunken they will be not, but the torment of Allah shall be severe"
  22,3,"And of mankind is he who disputeth respecting Allah without knowledge, and followeth any Satan froward"
  22,4,"Against whom it is prescribed, that: whosoever befriendeth him, him he shall lead astray and shall guide him on to the torment of the Flame"
  22,5,"O Mankind! if ye be in doubt respecting the Resurrection, then We have created you of the dust, then of a drop, then of clot, then of a piece of flesh, formed and unformed, that We might manifest unto you Our power. And We settle in the wombs that which We will until a term determined. Then We bring you forth as babes, then We let you reach your maturity. And of you is he who dieth, and of you is he who is brought back to the most abject age, so that after knowing he knoweth not aught. Andthou beholdest the earth withered up, and when We send down thereon water, it stirreth and swelleth, and it groweth every luxuriant kind of growth"
  22,6,"That, because Allah! He is The Truth, and He quickeneth the dead, and verily He is over everything Potent"
  22,7,And because the Hour is coming- there is no doubt thereof-- and because Allah will raise up those who are in the graves
  22,8,And of mankind is he who disputeth respecting Allah without knowledge or guidance or a Book luminous
  22,9,"Bending his neck, that he may lead astray from the way of Allah; his shall be humiliation in the world, and We shall make him taste on the Day of Judgment the torment of Burning"
  22,10,"That is because of that which thy hands have sent forth, and verily Allah is not a wronger of His bondmen"